body:
# A simple mod that makes mining more rewarding and enjoyable!
 

At this point, I would say you are tired of mining on minecraft right? This mods serves the purpose of making the mining experience less annoying, and also more rewarding, so players have a better time caving around.
 

## What the Mod Adds:
 

- 20 new enchantments including: Auto-Smelt, EXP and Jackpot;
- 10 modifiers that can be added appart from enchantments.
- 5 Repairing Stations to repair your tools based on different game mechanics;
- A Cobble Crusher to crush cobblestones and get extra ores;
- 2 new flowers that transform natural stone (and netherrack) into their respective ores;
- A new "Miner" villager profession with new trades;
- Fake Ores that damages the player when mined (there's an enchantment that disables them);
- Raw Debris, which now means that Fortune may work on Netherite;
- 3 new advancements to complete.
 



 

Note: By using the Enchantment Descriptions mod, all enchantments will have in-game descriptions starting on version 1.2.3 of this mod.
 

## Enchantments:
 

- Alchemist - gives a chance to turn copper into iron, and iron into gold. (Max Level: 1)
- Antidote - makes Fake Ores act like normal ores, whoever without any enchantment applied. (Max Level: 2)
- Auto-Smelt - instantly smelt any ore that needs to be smelted. (Max Level: 1)
- Chained Impact - adds a 25% chance of mining an adjacent block. (Max extra blocks broken are equivalent to the level.) (Max Level: 3)
- Deepslate Cracker - while mining deepslate or deepslate ores you get 20% more efficiency per level. (Max Level: 3)
- Energized - makes you immune to Mining Fatigue. (Max Level: 1)
- EXP - ores that drop experience points drop extra depending on the original value. (Max Level: 3)
- Graveller - instantly break any gravel overlapped with you. (Max Level: 2)
- Jackpot - you have a 25% chance to get double the max amount that the Fortune III enchantment grants you, or get absolutely nothing. (Max Level: 1)
- Moonbound - While it's night, you gain Speed I if holding the tool, aswell as +1 Fortune level on blocks you mine and makes the Midnight Blessing repairing station reapir the tool twice as fast. (Max Level: 1)
- Oversight - marks out any entity in a radius of 100 blocks. (Max Level: 1)
- Persistance - the more you mine, the faster you break. (Max Level: 4)
- Shatterstrike - The more durable the block you mine, the higher is the boost you gain to mine it. (Max Level: 3)
- Sunbound - While it's day, you gain Speed I if holding the tool, aswell as +1 Fortune level on blocks you mine and makes the Solar Blessing repairing station reapair the tool twice as fast. (Max Level: 1)
- Treasurer - you now have a chance to get ores by just mining stone, disable Fortune and Jackpot. (Max Level: 3)
- Torching - auto places torches if it's too dark in exchange of durability. (Max Level: 2)
- Vigor - deal extra damage if a pickaxe with this enchantment is on the off-hand. (+2 per level) (Max Level: 3)
- Warlock - gives a chance to add an effect to the player everytime a block is mined. (Max Level: 3)
- Curse of Unstability - makes the durability go down a random number every time you break something.
 

## Modifiers:
Modifiers can only be added to Netherite, Diamond and Iron.

 
- Sharpen Edge - gives plus 2 mining power to a pickaxe (found in Mineshafts or trading with the Miner);
- Hardened Crust - gives plus 800 durability (found in Mineshafts or trading with the Miner);
- Sharpener - gives plus 5 mining power but halves the durability (can only be crafted);
- Enchanting Catalyst - multiplies the enchantability (chance of getting good enchantments) by 2.5 times (found in Stronghold Libraries, Woodland Mansions or trading with the Miner);
- Magma Barrier - makes a Diamond or Iron pickaxe lava proof (found in Nether Fortresses);
- Double Edge - gives plus 8 mining power and 1000 more durability (can only be crafted);
- Chorus Crossing - Has 2 features: Firstly, by right clicking, you exchange some durability to throw an ender pearl, with 5 seconds of cooldown. Secondly, you have a 10% chance of when you try breaking a block, it teleports to a random (but close) location, similar to the chorus fruit effect (found in End Cities);
- Trader's Charm - has both a passive and active ability. Firstly, while having a pickaxe with the Trader's Charm modifier in your inventory, you permanently get Hero Of The Village I. Secondly, when mining, you have a chance for each ore you mine to drop an emerald, the rarer the ore, the higher the chance. (found in Woodland Mansions);
- Echo Chamber - adds a 40% chance to duplicate the drops of the ore you mine, including the effects of enchantments. (found in Ancient Cities);
- Eternal - makes the pickaxe unbreakable. (can only be crafted).
 

Repairing Stations:
Repairs tools inserted in them based on different game mechanics

 

- Solar Blessing - Repairs any tool inserted if in contact with daylight;
- Midnight Blessing - Repairs any tool inserted if in contact with moonlight;
- Magical Insight -  Restores the durability if it has energy, insert enchanted books to charge up;
- Volcanic Cage - Restores the durability if it has energy, insert furnace fuel items to charge it up;
- Windy Whetstone - Repairs the tool inside of it based on the height it is on, the higher, the faster it repairs.
 
 
## Ore Blooms:
Flowers representing each dimension that has ores.

- Ore Bloom - represents the Overworld. Turns Stone and Deepslate in a 3x3x3 area around it into overworld ores each 5 seconds. Rarer ores have less chance to appear;
- Infernal Ore Bloom - represents the Nether. Turns Netherrack in a 3x3x3 area around it into nether ores each 5 seconds. Has to be planted on Crimson or Warped Nylium.
 

Have any suggestions? Please message me on Discord (dorcamo) or leave it in the comments.
